{
  "stem": "3012.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I believe my maternal grandparents' grandparents came from northern Czechoslovakia, but everybody was born in Salgotarjan.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hungarian, and the grandfather's house sometimes we spoke German, with a little Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A little bit of Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Little bit of Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was an orthodox congregation, but in the strict sense, because, for example, when we went to the synagogue the women were sitting upstairs behind the-- not the bars, how do you call this in English?",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Behind the balustrade.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Probably.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the men were downstairs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there-- there-- there was also a segment of what you would call here Reformed Jewish entity, and the Orthodox entity.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One congregation, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Father-- every day, father was putting on the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had mezuzah on every door.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had a strict kosher household, and we duly observed Pesach.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the high holy days the business was closed, and father, along with his brothers, were praying in kittel.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "On Fridays-- on Saturdays our business was open.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Grandfather's business closed in the middle of Friday afternoon and stayed closed during the whole day of Saturday.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He went to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He put on the [NON-ENGLISH] every day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had the mezuzah on every single door.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he also wear the kittel in the-- during the-- the high holy days.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they always had the strictly kosher household, observing the Pesach, of course.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I really don't know, but-- but father and-- and grandfather felt that's how they want to do it, so they were doing it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I really don't have any idea how other people did it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in Salgotarjan, in my time, there were not-- no Jewish schools.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, we had the rabbi, who taught us liturgy and history, the Jewish law, and-- and every single thing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But not in school.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
